review_blob: Man I Really like this beer. This is the second time I have had it and maybe the second time is the charm.

First scotch style Ale Ive ever had. Im mostly a whiskey drinker and dont drink much craft beer. That said, this one had great body heavy caramel up front and a whiskey like finish. I like it alot. Hiccup.

Caramel is the only interesting flavor here. I drank it not knowing it was a Coors product and liked the up front Carmel flavor and the rich mouth feel of the foamy head. Past that there is no finish and a Coors light after taste. Ill finish the six pack but wont likely buy again.
Good beer, bought it at beer table in grand central. Citrus and wood make me think of summer nights. Is that enough Yayyyy.
